# Coding principles 
- Use Swift and SwiftUI for coding
- Use all SOLID pricnciple while implementig code
- Create a new file for new view
- Use MVVM architecture for development
- Follow Apple's Swift API Design Guidelines
- Use meaningful variable and function names
- Keep functions small and focused


# Documentation Rules
- Add debug logs for important operations
- Include comments explaining complex logic
- Document public interfaces and methods
- Use // MARK: for code section organization

# SwiftUI Best Practices
- Use PreviewProvider for all Views
- Keep View files under 300 lines when possible
- Extract reusable components into separate views
- Use proper view modifiers ordering
